HEADWORD: Epideictic
<hw>Ep`i*deic"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr.
<?/ to show forth, display; <grk>'epi`</grk> + <?/ to show. Cf.
<er>Epidictic</er>.]</ety> <def>Serving to show forth, explain, or
exhibit; -- applied by the Greeks to a kind of oratory, which, by full
amplification, seeks to persuade.</def></p>

